Interface Job

  • All Known Implementing Classes:

    public interface Job

      • end

        void end​(boolean normalCompletion)
        Ends processing for this job instance.
        Parameters:
        normalCompletion - Whether the executing engine reported normal completion for this job, or a failure (false).
        This value is used for calculating job status. If the engine reports a fault (false) the job will always gets JobStatus.ERROR. Otherwise the status results from the nJAMS events that have been generated during execution.

      • setStartTime

        void setStartTime​(LocalDateTime jobStart)
        Sets the start timestamp of a job.
        CAUTION:
        This method must not be called after the job has been started. If you need to set the job start explicitly, set it before you call start(). if you don't set the job start explicitly, it is set to the timestamp ob the job creation.
        Parameters:
        jobStart - job start

      • setStatus

void setStatus​(JobStatus status)
        Deprecated.
